---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL
---
<Layout title="ReqForge Documentation — Getting Started">
  <div class="container" style="display: flex; gap: 3rem;">
    <nav class="doc-sidebar">
      <h4>Getting Started</h4>
      <a href={`${base}docs/getting-started`} class="active">Installation & Quickstart</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/collections`}>Collections & Requests</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/environments`}>Environments & Variables</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/auth`}>Authentication</a>
      <h4>Guides</h4>
      <a href={`${base}docs/testing`}>Testing & Scripts</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/import-export`}>Importing & Exporting</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/plugins`}>Plugin Development</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/sync`}>Cloud Sync</a>
      <h4>Reference</h4>
      <a href={`${base}docs/cli`}>CLI Reference</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/keyboard`}>Keyboard Shortcuts</a>
      <a href={`${base}docs/troubleshooting`}>Troubleshooting</a>
    </nav>
    <article class="doc-content">
      <h1>Welcome to ReqForge</h1>
      <p>
        ReqForge is an open-source, cross-platform API development platform.
        It ships as a native desktop app (Windows, macOS, Linux) and a command-line
        tool. Everything works offline — no account required.
      </p>

      <h2>Quick Install</h2>
      <pre># macOS (Homebrew)
brew install reqforge/tap/reqforge

# Windows (winget)
winget install reqforge

# Linux (deb)
curl -sSL https://get.reqforge.io | sh

# Or download binaries from GitHub Releases:
# https://github.com/reqforge/reqforge/releases</pre>

      <h2>Your First Request</h2>
      <pre>1. Open ReqForge
2. Type https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos/1 in the URL bar
3. Click Send
4. See the JSON response in the response panel</pre>

      <p>That's it. You just sent your first request.</p>

      <h2>Importing Existing Collections</h2>
      <p>
        ReqForge can import collections from Postman, cURL, Insomnia, and Bruno:
      </p>
      <pre># Postman v2.1 — File → Import → Postman
# cURL — Paste your curl command directly into the URL bar
# Insomnia — File → Import → Insomnia
# Bruno — File → Import → Bruno</pre>

      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href={`${base}docs/collections`}>Organize requests into collections</a></li>
        <li><a href={`${base}docs/environments`}>Set up environments with variables</a></li>
        <li><a href={`${base}docs/auth`}>Configure authentication</a></li>
        <li><a href={`${base}docs/testing`}>Write test assertions</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
